<h1>
  Class c2.framework.Brick
</h1>
<pre>
<a href="java.lang.Object.html#_top_">java.lang.Object</a>
   |
   +----c2.framework.Brick
</pre>
<hr>
<dl>
  <dt> public class <b>Brick</b>
  <dt> extends <a href="java.lang.Object.html#_top_">Object</a>
</dl>
Brick is the abstract super class of both components and connectors.  It
contains data and behavior that is shared between the two. <p>
NOTE: This class should not be used directly.  Use either Component,
Connector, or one of their derived classes.
<dl>
    <dt> <b>See Also:</b>
    <dd> <a href="c2.framework.Component.html#_top_">Component</a>, <a href="c2.framework.Connector.html#_top_">Connector</a>, <a href="c2.framework.ComponentThread.html#_top_">ComponentThread</a>, <a href="c2.framework.ConnectorThread.html#_top_">ConnectorThread</a>
</dl>
