<a name="newMessage(c2.framework.Port)"><img src="images/red-ball.gif" width=12 height=12 alt=" o "></a>
<a name="newMessage"><b>newMessage</b></a>
<pre>
  protected abstract void newMessage(<a href="c2.framework.Port.html#_top_">Port</a> p)
</pre>
<dl>
  <dd> This method is invoked when the brick receives a new request or
notification.  By default, it invokes the appropriate handle() method.
Override this function only if you need to do special processing on
incomming messages.
  <dl>
    <dt> <b>See Also:</b>
    <dd> <a href="c2.framework.Component.html#handle">handle</a>, <a href="c2.framework.Connector.html#handle">handle</a>
  </dl>
</dl>
